.{display}

Display Modes

block
inline
inline-block
flex
inline-flex
table
table-row
table-cell
hidden


In css most things are actually block.

This is gonna be in block (one on top of the other)

<body>
    <div>Hello <div class="bg-yellow-300 w-32 h-6">World!</div></div>
</body>

But if you add inline to the second div will be inline

<body>
  <div>Hello <div class="bg-yellow-300 w-32 h-6 inline">World!</div></div>
</body>

and use inline-block to respect the width of the container

HIDING AN ELEMENT


<body>
     <div>Hello <div class="bg-yellow-300 w-32 h-6 hidden">World!</div></div>
</body>
